choices.text:
still missing spare hours (and hours but… well…). It is more stressful than in childhood (even while working at a full time job), I think it comes from responsibility, priorities and priorities to be maintained (household, family, social and others) [to do things that matter you have to be focused!]. Besides I feel more empathy for other people: the guy who takes shit at school or work, the old lady in my group (60+ members) who walks in, the three hours ahead at night guy and every one other who attends same or similar attacks every day. Well and – did you ever sit in a train for more than two hours, coming home knowing that you have two hours sleep left till waking up? I hate it.

In fact I became much more relaxed and was able to enjoy so many things I missed in childhood: beer and wine, being drunk, just partying! 😀

So my points:

– the different phases before, during and after (adult) puberty fit well to the triple bunk boxes, with the overview in the middle box.

– managing a time adequate for the boxes peaks not all boxes at the same time, but its varing over the ones right next to eachother.

– sioclippers can fit a lot on the wall, too [especially where trays are needed too!]
